```css .row { display: flex; justify-content: flex-end; } .row div { margin-right: 10px; /* Add spacing between divs */ } ``` **Explanation:** * **`.row`**: This selector targets the container holding the divs. * **`display: flex;`**: This line is crucial as it tells the browser to treat this element as a flexbox container. * **`justify-content: flex-end;`**: This property aligns the items (the divs) within the container to the end of the flex line, effectively aligning them to the right. **HTML Example:** ```html
Div 1
Div 2
Div 3
```
